text: Antonín Šponar (8 April 1920 - November 2002) was a Czech alpine skier. He competed in three events at the 1948 Winter Olympics. ==References== Category:1920 births Category:2002 deaths Category:Czech male alpine skiers Category:Olympic alpine skiers of Czechoslovakia Category:Alpine skiers at the 1948 Winter Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Prague
